cs.AR, cs.ET, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LG 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) because it proposes a novel approximate computing architecture with a Multiclass-Classifier and Multiple Approximators (MCMA) that can share the same hardware resource in a neural processing unit (NPU) clip. It is also likely to belong to cs.ET (Embedded Systems) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) because it deals with energy-efficient computing and runtime swapping of approximators. Additionally, it may belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) because it proposes efficient co-training methods for the MCMA architecture and deals with neural approximators and classifiers.
